modules.description: Loads and decodes image files from memory, supporting common formats like PNG and JPEG. It provides functions to retrieve pixel data as arrays, along with dimensions and color channel information. Used to integrate external images into rendering pipelines or image processing workflows.

This module offers image processing capabilities including loading, decoding, and applying effects like mipmap generation and blur, utilizing 8-bit and 32-bit float Bigarray buffers for efficient data handling. It provides type aliases and low-level memory management for binary image data, supporting tasks such as dimension manipulation and pixel-level operations. Use cases include real-time image rendering, texture generation, and memory-sensitive image transformations.
